title: American Horror Stories: “Rubber(wo)Man” BREAKDOWN Episode 1 & 2
author: GameSpot Universe
comment: why was everyone so ok with being dead? like it felt so sudden that they were like “welp guess we’re dead now” and become some messed up modern family
The episode was…. Fine. And that’s okay, if every episode is just as good or better I’ll be very happy I just hope it doesn’t get worse from here on out

I'm just really annoyed they followed the general first season almost exactly. Murderer in the suit, a gay couple gets murdered, the parents are already dead like violet, psycho ghost who wants them to join them forever like tate, vengeful ghosts that didnt expect to be murdered like the group of girls. Like come ON, there was other things they really could've done but they really just copied it
I absolutely loved when I heard young Adelaide’s voice say “you’re going to die in there.” One of my favorite little scenes from Murder House. She is adorable.
For having to wait over a wholeeeeeeee year,  I was very disappointed. The plot in my head was much better.
description:
Greg is back to break down the first two episodes of Ryan Murphy’s new anthology series: American Horror Stories! This video will take a closer look at the premiere episode: "Rubber(wo)Man", and also point out all the easter eggs and references we could find so far.
